The Zondo Commission of Inquiry into state capture resumes on Thursday. Editor's note: The commission has adjourned for lunch. It is expected to resume at 2pm. Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Former KZN Hawks head Johan Booysen returns to the stand at the state capture inquiry. Booysen linked two Zuma relatives to controversial businessman Thoshan Panday. During his testimony last month, he testified that he visited Nkandla twice to flag the issue with former president Jacob Zuma. READ: Booysen links Zuma relatives to controversial businessman He said Edward Zuma asked him to unfreeze R15-million because he was in business with Panday. Booysen was arrested in 2012, accused of heading the so-called “Cato Manor death squad”.